The Herald Who manufactured the vaccine?
Chinese State-owned enterprise Sinopharm developed China’s first approved Covid-19 vaccine which is based on an inactivated virus. Sinopharm developed it in collaboration with the Wuhan Institute of Virology and the Institute of Biological Products. Has the vaccine been used elsewhere? By the end of last year, nearly 100 million doses had been produced and production is expected to reach one billion doses this year. The Sinopharm vaccine is approved in China for general public use and is also used in several other countries including the United Arab Emirates (UAE). According to Sinopharm website, more than 50 countries have expressed willingness to procure the vaccine. What have other countries said about the vaccine’s effectiveness? According to the UAE’s health ministry, the Sinopharm vaccine has proven to be 86 percent effective in preventing moderate and severe cases of the disease. Have any African countries used and reviewed the drug? Early this year, Egypt started vaccinating medical staff at public hospitals, armed forces and police with the Chinese vaccine and its health minister said clinical trials had proved it’s safe and effective. Morocco has also administered the drug with no problems.